  "prompt": "How much should I aim in my graduation to get into IIM A/B/C assuming I get a 99+ percentile in CAT?",
  "response": "To enhance your chances of admission to the Indian Institutes of Management (IIM) Ahmedabad, Bangalore, or Calcutta (often referred to as IIM A, B, and C), a good academic record is important, along with a high CAT score. While a 99+ percentile in CAT is a significant achievement, the IIMs will also consider your overall profile, which includes:\n\n1. **Undergraduate Percentage**: Typically, aiming for an undergraduate percentage of 80% or above is advisable. However, the exact requirement can vary depending on your background (engineering, commerce, arts, etc.). For IIM A/B/C, 85% and above will strengthen your application significantly.\n\n2. **Work Experience**: Relevant work experience can add value to your profile. While freshers are accepted, candidates with work experience are often preferred.\n\n3. **Diversity Factors**: Candidates from diverse academic backgrounds (non-engineering, for example) can get some advantages in the selection process.\n\n4. **Other Achievements**: Extracurricular activities, leadership roles, and achievements (academic or otherwise) can also enhance your profile.\n\n5. **Personal Interview (PI) and Written Ability Test (WAT)**: Performing well in these rounds is crucial for final selection, regardless of your academic performance or CAT scores.\n\nIn summary, aim for at least 80-85% in your graduation, ideally 85% or higher, while also focusing on other aspects of your application to strengthen your chances of getting into IIM A/B/C with a 99+ percentile in CAT.",
